OL,6,FAngela Madden, chairwoman of Waspi,
OL,7,Fsaid: "The Government has an
OL,8,Fopportunity now to get around the
OL,9,Ftable and engage meaningfully with us.
OL,10,FIf they don't, they will have to
OL,11,Fcontinue to defend the indefensible,
OL,12,Fbut this time in front of senior
OL,13,Fjudges."
OL,15,FA Government spokesperson said: "We do
OL,16,Fnot comment on live litigation.
OL,18,F"We accept the ombudsman's finding of
OL,19,Fmaladministration and have apologised
OL,20,Ffor there being a 28-month delay in
OL,21,Fwriting to 1950s-born women.
